Package: fxruby-ruby1.6
Version: 1.0.23
Revision: 1
Description: Fox bindings for Ruby
License: LGPL
Maintainer: Michal Suchanek <Hramrach@centrum.cz>
Depends: fox1-shlibs, ruby16-shlibs
BuildDepends: fox1, fxscintilla, ruby16-dev
Provides: fxruby
Source: mirror:sourceforge:fxruby/FXRuby-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 91fa3a2d5924577b98c58106ae9fe4da
SetCC: gcc3
SetCXX: g++3
GCC: 3.1
SetLDFLAGS: -no-undefined
CompileScript: <<
ruby install.rb config -- --with-fox-include=%p/include/fox --with-fox-lib=%p/lib --with-fxscintilla --with-fxscintilla-include=%p/include/fxscintilla
ruby install.rb setup
<<
InstallScript: <<
ruby install.rb install --prefix=%d
install -d %i/share/doc/%n
cp -r doc %i/share/doc/%n/html
cp -r examples %i/share/doc/%n
chown -R root.admin %i/share/doc/%n/html %i/share/doc/%n/examples
<<
DocFiles: ANNOUNCE ChangeLog INSTALL LICENSE README
DescDetail: <<
Fox is a GUI toolkit written in C++, FXRuby are ruby bindings for Fox.
It is used by FreeRIDE, the ruby IDE.
<<
DescPackaging: <<
It uses fox which has to be compiled with g++3 (or with gcc2 and very
different options) so gcc3 has to be used for this package.
How to install a documentation directory without chown?
<<
HomePage: http://www.fxruby.org
